urlText: Trackwork between Bankstown and Sydenham
content:
Monday 28 June to Friday 2 July
  • Buses replace trains between Bankstown and Sydenham. Find out more.
  • Trains run to a changed timetable between Bankstown and Lidcombe only. You can change at Lidcombe for trains towards the City.
  • Trains also run between Liverpool and the City via Regents Park. Change at Regents Park if you are travelling between stations Liverpool and Sefton to stations between Birrong and Sydenham.
  • All-stations buses run between Bankstown and Sydenham, but for a faster trip to and from the City, extra express buses run to and from the following stations:
    • Bankstown, catch bus 52T3 to Padstow then change for a train.
    • Punchbowl or Wiley Park, catch bus 53T3 to Beverly Hills then change for a train.
    • Lakemba or Belmore, catch bus 54T3 to Kingsgrove then change for a train.
    • Campsie or Canterbury, catch express bus 74T3 or 55T3 to Central.
    • Hurlstone Park, Dulwich Hill or Marrickville, catch bus route 10T3 to Sydenham then change for a train.
  • Extra trains run on the T8 Airport & South Line to connect with replacement buses to or from Padstow, Beverly Hills or Kingsgrove. Some trains run via Sydenham and make extra stops at St Peters and Erskineville.
  • If you are travelling from the City to stations Belmore to Bankstown please catch a T8 Airport & South Line train to Kingsgrove, Beverly Hills or Padstow and change for an express bus. Only all-stations buses leave from Sydenham.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
Bus routes

10T3: Bankstown, then all stations to Sydenham and return
51T3: Hurlstone Park, then all stations to Sydenham and return
52T3: Bankstown to Padstow express and return
53T3: Punchbowl, Wiley Park then Beverly Hills and return
54T3: Lakemba, Belmore then Kingsgrove and return
55T3: Canterbury to Central express and return
74T3: Campsie to Central express and return
subtitle: Trackwork between Bankstown and Sydenham

  • Buses replace trains between Sydenham and Central, and between Central and Bondi Junction.
  • Trains run to a changed timetable between:
    • Cronulla and Sydenham
    • Waterfall and Hurstville
  • If you are travelling to the City from Illawarra Line stations please change at Wolli Creek for a T8 Airport & South Line train to City Circle stations.
  • Change at Central for buses to Kings Cross, Edgecliff or Bondi Junction.
  • Trackwork buses do not leave from Martin Place Station. Sydney Buses services leave from nearby bus stops or you can catch the light rail to Town Hall or Central.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.

urlText: Trackwork may affect your travel
content:
Monday 12 to Thursday 15 July
  • From 1.15pm Monday, buses replace trains between Bomaderry and Kiama.
  • From 3pm Monday until 3.30am Thursday, buses replace trains between Bomaderry and Dapto.
  • Buses travelling towards Dapto may leave from stations Bomaderry to Albion Park up to 40 minutes earlier than the normal train timetable.
  • Most trains run to the normal timetable between Dapto and Central or Bondi Junction.
  • On Thursday from 3.30am until 12pm, buses replace trains between Bomaderry and Kiama only.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
